<HR size="1" color="#dedfdf">
<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">
My main character is a level 60 necromancer, I soloed most of the way up to 60, pretty much only grouping from 48-52 and 56-60.<P>The exp was fast and fun. If I died I would have to learn from my mistakes, and only blame it on myself.<P>Once I hit 60, I decided to make a warrior twink. I farmed sebilis in groups, literally, for two months. Got him fungi tunic, lam, WS, Tant tusk, 3 pieces of cobalt.. nice gear..<P>I am now level 38. I recently went into sol b. After grouping for 15 minutes, the cleric decided to 'leave' to go to the Bat 1 group that wanted him (He was 42). We were stuck getting Crap exp since we had no healer. <P>Enchanter disbanded to leave to KPC and monk logged... I disbanded and tried for a group.<BR>30 minutes passed, was still ungrouped. I pulled a single GK, got it to 5% then it started running, and was healed 3 times by a kobold shaman. Had to zone, since I was now slowed and it was running god knows where.<P>My questions.<BR>1.) Why do we 'have to group' if we are a lesser class, such as warriors and rangers are?<BR>2.) Why is group exp *SOOOOOOOOOOOOO* slow compared to solo exp? It takes longer to get a group, and group people get you trained a lot which takes even more time. I don't know how people levle from 50-60 in Karnors I got almost three times as much exp at 54 on Raptors than I did in a KC group.<BR>3.) Why can't warriors solo? In most online games, we do not 'have' to group. If we want to group, we can. We aren't 'forced' to group.<BR>4.) Why can't we bind/gate? As much as I love walking 4 zones to seek a group for 30 minutes then have it disband, then go back to EC and try and trade stuff off (am a twink, you know)... not my idea of fun...<BR>5.) Why are we *REQUIRED* to group? Seriously, it does not add to roleplaying experience. A necromancer can root + dot 3 raptors at once, whereas my warrior could probaly not solo a raptor at level 60 (Geez, would SUCK if they fled he'd aggro whole isle)<P>Baradak 38 warrior 7th Hammer, frustrated Twink awaiting Dark Age of Camelot.
</FONT>
