<HR size="1" color="#dedfdf">
<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">
So many things wrong with this discussion that I won't get really upset and express my feelings except to say, it's a mutliplayer game for a reason, and your limitations as a warrior make him kinda need a group (PS a troll warrior has faster hp regen)... <P>Now to answer your questions..<BR>1.) Why do we 'have to group' if we are a lesser class, such as warriors and rangers are?<BR>** You don't have to group, you just will be more successful because of your limitations if you do...**<P>2.) Why is group exp *SOOOOOOOOOOOOO* slow compared to solo exp? It takes longer to get a group, and group people get you trained a lot which takes even more time. I don't know how people levle from 50-60 in Karnors I got almost three times as much exp at 54 on Raptors than I did in a KC group.<BR>**The experience isn't any slower, excepting if their is a exp penalty for your race, it just may seem that way because you DEPEND on others (just like they depend on warriors as a meat shield).**<P>3.) Why can't warriors solo? In most online games, we do not 'have' to group. If we want to group, we can. We aren't 'forced' to group.<BR>**This isn't most online games, and if you really wanted to solo then you wouldn't have bought a mutli-player game, now would you??**<P>4.) Why can't we bind/gate? As much as I love walking 4 zones to seek a group for 30 minutes then have it disband, then go back to EC and try and trade stuff off (am a twink, you know)... not my idea of fun...<BR>**My opinion of twinking and farming is that neither of them is fun or challenging, but that also is another point... As far as why warriors can't bind/gate, it's because they have no magic ability.. If you wanted someone who binded or gated you picked the wrong class.. **<BR> <BR>5.) Why are we *REQUIRED* to group? Seriously, it does not add to roleplaying experience. A necromancer can root + dot 3 raptors at once, whereas my warrior could probaly not solo a raptor at level 60 (Geez, would SUCK if they fled he'd aggro whole isle)<BR>**Required grouping was something that they added to this game to make up for the limitations of each class... The warrior can't heal himself or cast magic so therefore he sort of needs assistance from others... I really don't see a reason why you'd want to play a mutli-player game, seeing your attitude is only about soloing.. You really should go back to Diablo, or create the only other EQ character who has solo capability, a druid...**<P>--------------------<P> <IMG SRC="http://www.monmouth.com/~robertl/images/rotateyy.gif"> <P>Humans Learn from the Earth<BR>The Earth follows The Heavens..
</FONT>
