<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">
In response to the solo vs grouping issue, let me give you a bit of history from another game I used to play.<P>In this other world, the grouping system was broken, IMO. While there were several mobs that required a group effort to bring down, due to the lacking in-game system it became a race for all partied involved to kill the mob, get the most damage, secure loot rights etc. This ruined grouping for me and I was forced to find solice hunting alone.<P>Now correct me if I'm wrong, but most people, myself included, play MMORPGS for the interaction of other humans (in toon form or not, they are still there behind the keyboard)<P>Without this interaction, we might as well be playing a single player game. While its nice that there are classes/techniques that allow you to solo, IMO, the cornerstone of EQ is built on the grouping experience.<P>Again, just my 2cp, Good Day   <IMG SRC="biggrin.gif" border="0"><P>--------------------<P>Golox, Halfling Druid of Xev<P>Formerly Darven the Bard
