<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">
The game for me is the grouping - as a lvl 42 shaman I can solo stuff - difficult as I have to hunt weak blues and the odd green that give experience.  In a group I can really start to play the role, buff, heal, slow, speed up and DOT - plus for me the real fun is the grouping - you chat - have laughs - etc....<P>I am sure that I could get to where I am now if I had solod - it would have taken a while longer but I am happier in the group.  I got more exp and loot from grouping that I would get from soloing - plus I can see places that I would just be killed on the spot in at a slightly lower level.<P>Why as some people have said play a online game like EQ when you resent grouping ?? <P>To get a good group - well you have to be slightly picky and make sure the people you group with have the same objectives you have and if it works then you can group time and time again.  I have several people I regularly group with who arent always on line when I am there but most of the time I can find a good group.  I would never turn down a good warrior - tanks can really speed up the combats, and a few good tanks can reduce down time and turn single pulling into a continuous melee.<P>--------------------<P>Shaman of 45 seasons<BR>Rogue of 18 seasons<BR>Enchanter of 14 seasons
