<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">
I hear people on these boards complain often about not being able to solo.  I guess I've just never understood the concept behind their concerns.  If you want to play by yourself, in your own little world, there are any number of games out there where you can do that.  IMHO, the best thing about EQ is the grouping experience.  I know this is just my preference, but I play to group.  I don't like soloing, never have.  It's the actual grouping experience that makes me want to keep playing.  <P>If you wanted to solo, quite frankly, you bought the wrong game.  It would be like buying a Play Station and Final Fantasy and then turning it on and looking for a group.  EQ is not about soloing, and Verant will make that perfectly clear.  They don't hide behind false truths about the true nature of the game, and tell you straight out that this game has been made to encourage grouping.<P>You group in EQ, you don't solo, that is its underlying foundation.  I would seriously look into another game if you want to solo, and stop worrying about why EQ isn't the type of game it wasn't designed to be.<P>Just my opinion.
</FONT>
