If you could pick any class you wanted, and solo with that class, you'd never get a camp again, you'd be fighting and bickering over wandering mobs . . . <P>Okay, standard scenario:<P>Rathe Mountains, HG area.  3 groups, 3 necros.  The 3 groups consist of 4, 3 and 5 people, the 3 necros are soloing, each of the 6 "groups" (counting 1 necro as 1 group) is pulling and killing HGs are a fairly even pace, not leaving much for any more groups or soloers.  Result: 15 people hunting in one area.<P>Your way: 3 warriors and 3 necros are all soloing HGs, pretty much not leaving any for others.  Result: 6 players hunting in 1 area.<P>Instead of 2500 people split up into 700 "groups" (people who group and people who solo), you would have 2400 individual "groups."  And you think getting a camp is bad NOW?   <IMG SRC="eek.gif" border="0"><P>--------------------<P>Players on EverQuest:<BR>---------------------------<BR>[51 Reaver] Bhah (Ogre) <BR>There is 1 player in Twilight Zone.
