LOL if you realy want to solo, I will trade my lvl 50 wizard for any lvl 35 or better tank in a hart beat.<P>Here is why soloing is difficult for a tank.<P>To be a tank you give up any magic casting abilities, this is in exchange for the following:<P>1. ) Masiv HP<BR>2. ) Masiv AC though the use of items.<BR>3. ) Masiv defensive and offensive abilities.<P>Furthermore if you want to solo as a tank, max out your bandage skill and get some items with magic effects such as Jboots, stun whip, and haste tiems. With these tiems you can do a form a kiting and solo low blue con mobs. Then you will be able to solo and you sill still be one of the most damaging classes in the game post lvl 40. Any tank class can out damage any caster in the post 50 game by at lest a 3 to one ratio over a one hour time frame and when the mobs are highly magic resistant that goes up to a 6 to one ratio.<P>I cant belive you are bitching about being LFG for 30 min. The average time I spend LFG with my wizard is 2 hours and on several occasions I have been LFG for up to 7 hours. This was not becuase the zones were just packed, I saw many tanks, healer, and buffers get into groups while I was waiting.<P>A tank can always get a combination of items that will let them solo, and they will still be very effective in groups. Most Casters can solo very low blue con mobs, but there are no items that will make a caster sigificantly more effective in groups.
