MAlt wrote<P>I hear people on these boards complain often about not being able to solo. I guess I've just never understood the concept behind their concerns. If you want to play by yourself, in your own little world, there are any number of games out there where you can do that. IMHO, the best thing about EQ is the grouping experience. I know this is just my preference, but I play to group. I don't like soloing, never have. It's the actual grouping experience that makes me want to keep playing. <P><BR>I understand your point, but I like to solo. Just becuse I like to solo doesnt mean I want to be in my own little world. I like the interaction and seeing other players and chatting with the, ..I just prefer to fight alone. Doesnt mean Im anti-social I like the fact that EQ is MMORPG..that doesnt mean I have to have somebody with me 24-7 to enjoy the game. I like to adventure alone. and not have to worry about a group lagging behind me or getting lost. I also group, but not all the time. Hey for me its like real life..I hang out alot with friends..but i like the adventure of going to a new place alone. Thats ust how I am..and that crosses over for me in EQ. AS for classes I chose A class that I cold solo with over grouping (51 Mage now).  Just dont make assumptions about people becasue they would rather not group. I like the interaction with players on my downtime,but for the most part I like to be alone(RP that way too..loner) Thats why I play I get the best of both worlds interaction when needed and solutide when called for. You do Have a choice. I have watchd post 50 warr solo stuff..a bit hard..but i have seen it(although limted places) you just have to be equpped for it(sow potions...heal potions or items..or just ask a passing by healer)<P>Enjoy the game..casue thats what it is. Some people look at it like a job. I play for fun and nothing else. Im not worried about Phat Lewtz or my Uber factor. Im just another part of the world  <IMG SRC="smile.gif" border="0"><