<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">
Let me try to preface this with I dont like to solo, I HATE to solo, if I wanted to solo, I would have stuck with Might and Magic 7 and 8.  With that in mind, I think all classes should be able to solo about on par with each other.<P>If there is "class balance", then any class should be able to solo and advance at approximately same level.  I dont care what class wins in a duel...we fight mobs for exp and loot (on care-bear servers we do).  Since the majaority of servers are PvE, we should have the same equal chance to solo for those that wish to do so.<P>For those that do not live, eat, and breathe EQ, they ALL deserve the same chance others do.  If someone logs on for 1 hour, they should be able to fight as well as any other class.  No, a pali shouldnt fight as well as a warrior, but the combo fight and self heal should = roughly same down time as better warrior that needs to sit to heal naturally.<P>If Verant wants the majority of players to group, there should be enough benefit to encourage grouping more than punishment for not doing it.  Also, get rid of the fear of grouping...for starters REAL punishment of "ninja looters".  Want to see less farming ladies and gentlemen?  Most would group for items like SMR if they were not afraid someone would ninja loot it if it dropped.<P>To the original poster, a warrior can solo effectively...but key is WHERE to solo.  Sol a and b both are notorious places for even balanced groups to die because of pathing, lava, goblins passing agro, trains, etc.<P>--------------------<P>Burzug Ironfyst, Paladin, Rodcet Nife<BR>"It is an honour to serve others"
