<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">
From a cleric's perspective:<P>I HATE leaving groups when I actually have to go. I won't leave a group for a different area unless the current group is packed full or morons or is in the process of killing me. <P>The issue that most people fail to see is that clerics and enchanters are people too. If we have to go, we have to go. I have work in the mornings and can't stay up for long raids with my guild. Does that make me evil? No. Does that make me a snooty cleric? No. It just makes me a person. The thing that kills me is that because of our enhanced healing abilities (15% over other healing classes), we're seen as the only people who can heal. Now, if the cleric has to go, why not get a druid or a shaman to take her place? It's not the end of the world and that is why Verant gave druids/shaman more healing spells.<P>The same goes for warriors... if the warrior leaves, oopsie, no tank... gotta fight all the way to the top of OS or evac/succor out. <P>It's a pain in the neck, but the high-end game relies on players having to group up. The creatures have far too many hitpoints to solo as no one, even a wizard, doesn't have enough mana to burn on those bad boys to kill them. Also, the creatures hit far too hard for anyone to solo them.<P>You HAVE to group  <IMG SRC="frown.gif" border="0"> unless of course you go to Skyfire as a necro or a druid eh... then you can kite ... which really pisses me off.  <IMG SRC="mad.gif" border="0"><P>--------------------<P>Georgia Gaelicmyst<BR>Cleric of Tunare <BR>Fennin Ro Server<BR>Caster's Realm Moderator
